The paper proposes a deep learning framework for land cover mapping using multi-source and multi-temporal satellite images. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of domain expert knowledge to guide the model initialization, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new pretraining strategy and attention mechanism, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
